{
  "texts": [
    "This is in line with the clinical observation that the glycerol level in GBM patients is much higher in tumors compared to normal tissue in the tumor periphery 49.",
    "It was also reported that brain metastasis also upregulates lipid metabolism 50, 51, indicating an adaptation of cancer cells to the lipid-deprived brain environment 50, 52.",
    "For this purpose, brain tumor cells upregulate GPD1 to switch the metabolic flow to lipid metabolism by making use of the glycolysis metabolite DHAP, which was also reported to be the only sensor metabolite of the mTOR pathway in glycolysis 53.",
    "More importantly, 6, and Table 7.",
    "we also discovered that MTTP inhibitor Lomitapide efficiently blocks LEGO growth, providing another attractive target, and the drug should be further investigated."
  ]
}